					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, but the lower line of the MMC1 CHR registers would just be a plain copy of PPU A12 if you set MMC1 in 8kb CHR-switching mode.
<br />
<br />So to use it as a latch you'd *have* to set the MMC1 in 4kb CHR-switching mode, and always set both Reg1 and Reg2 the same value, so that this latched value is constant on MMC1's CHR-A12 line.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
